take accurate measurement of max acceleration and then use alpha = a/r to accurately find the max angular acceleration
tasks.text_content:
https://softschools.com/formulas/physics/torque_formula/59/
you want τ = Iα
torque = momentOfInertia * angularAcceleration
torque = radius x force
force, in this case, is what the wheel exerts on the carpet (well, all four wheels)
radius is between the wheel's contact patch and the center of rotation of the robot (on the floor)
this shouldn't be mixed up with the torque of the motor, which is what eventually gets converted into a force by the wheel (the wheel is a spinning-to-linear converter), but that's where your force term comes from
